fr.reflexe.viewshell.api.design

Interface IFormPage

  • All Superinterfaces:
    IAuthenticatedPage, IDataPage, IThemedPage

    public interface IFormPage
extends IDataPage, IAuthenticatedPage
    Provides data for a form page for an authenticated user, for viewing, editing, or creating a record.

    Thread-safety: implementations of this interface are not required to be safe for concurrent access. Therefore, processing should generally not be shared between multiple threads.

    Since:
    1.0
    Author:
    REFLEXE Technologies
    See Also:
    IFormDesign

    • Method Detail

      • setPageContext

        void setPageContext(IFormContext context)
             throws IllegalStateException
        Sets the context for page processing and rendering, after this page instance has been selected. This should only be called (at most) once per instance. If this instance is not selected (if overridden, or if used for constructing a page URI), then it might never be invoked.
        Parameters:
        context - the non-null context.
        Throws:
        IllegalStateException - if invoked more than once.
        Since:
        1.0

      • adapt

        IFormPage adapt(EnumSet<Defer> defer)
         throws UnsupportedOperationException
        Gets a derived version of this form page, specifying optional deferred retrieval of certain categories of data.

        If the specified options match current options, then invoking this method has no effect (the returned instance will be the current instance).

        The master item will be fetched again (with the specified deferral options) by the adapted instance, when getMasterItem() is invoked.

        Parameters:
        defer - the non-null set of deferral options.
        Returns:
        the adapted instance.
        Throws:
        UnsupportedOperationException - if this form page is to be used to create a new item for the master source.
        Since:
        1.0

      • getMasterKey

        IKey getMasterKey()
        Gets the key of the master item, the main record for the form page. This does not necessarily involve a fetch operation.
        Returns:
        the key of the master item.
        Since:
        1.0
        See Also:

      • getMasterItem

        IItem getMasterItem()
             throws FetchException
        Gets the master item, the main record for the form page. For an existing item, this will normally involve a fetch operation to retrieve the data. When a fetch operation is involved, the afterDataItemFetch method is invoked on registered page processors by default implementations of this interface.

        Other items may include associated ascending items, descending items, or embedded items (such as array data). These other items are available via the data cells of the master item. Fetching may be eager or may be deferred.

        Returns:
        the master item.
        Throws:
        FetchException - if the item cannot be fetched.
        Since:
        1.0
        See Also:
        getMasterKey(), isCreateForm()

      • isCreateForm

        boolean isCreateForm()
        Indicates if this form page is to be used to create a new item for the master source. When creating a new item record, the master item will be null. The master source can normally be used to determine the item structure for creating a new record.
        Returns:
        true if this is a form for creating a new item, or false if the form is for viewing or editing an existing item.
        Since:
        1.0
